<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm368440400">
<term>allocated costs</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm384495280">costs that are generated by non–revenue generating portions of the business, such as corporate headquarters, that are assigned based on some formula to the revenue generating portions of the business</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm344373568">
<term>segment</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm380467488">portion of the business that management believes has sufficient similarities in product lines, geographic locations, or customers to warrant reporting that portion of the company as a distinct part of the entire company</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
